Significant modifications by the JetAuth Contributors include, but are not
limited to:

  - Go module path renamed to github.com/deluxebear/jetauth.
  - Rebranded as JetAuth.
  - New frontend in web/ built with React, Vite, Tailwind CSS v4, and
    TanStack Query, replacing the upstream Ant Design frontend.
  - Business-permission (ReBAC) subsystem, including per-application Casbin
    policy tables, role inheritance propagation, and a resource catalog
    with OpenAPI/CSV/YAML/JSON/paste import.
  - Built-in RADIUS server removed (upstream module had latent correctness
    bugs and PAP-only support).
  - Security fix: entity update APIs prevent owner-field tampering across
    organization boundaries.
  - SQLite driver upgraded to modernc.org/sqlite v1.48.2 (SQLite 3.51, JSONB).
  - Additional hardening, observability, and admin-UX changes documented in
    docs/ and the project CHANGELOG.

